    <ns3:mutableNotes>References (unparsed) here: &lt;p&gt;Elowitz, M.B., Leibler, S. A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional      regulators. &lt;em&gt;Nature&lt;/em&gt; 403, 335-338 (2000). &lt;a href="http://biobricks.ai.mit.edu/BB_References.htm#ELOW00"&gt;[ELOW00]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;     &lt;br&gt;   &lt;/P&gt; &lt;P&gt; References (unparsed) here: &lt;p&gt;Elowitz, M.B., Leibler, S. A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional      regulators. &lt;em&gt;Nature&lt;/em&gt; 403, 335-338 (2000). &lt;a href="http://biobricks.ai.mit.edu/BB_References.htm#ELOW00"&gt;[ELOW00]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;     &lt;br&gt;   &lt;/P&gt; &lt;P&gt;Sequence taken from the repressilator of Elowitz and Leibler (2000). The obtained      sequence was compared to the wild-type sequence for LacI obtained through      a database search. The sequence had been modified from the wild-type in that      wild-type GTG start was changed to an ATG start (note, actual ORF in E.coli      has several GTG starts it would seem). The LVA tag has been added for quicker      degradation.&lt;P&gt; Incompatible with systems containing LacI, lactose, or IPTG.
</ns3:mutableNotes>
